main event: On 12 September 1956, an object shaped like a cigar was observed in Rossville, Georgia.
interesting points: The object moved from S.S.W. to W., disappearing in three to five minutes,The size of the object was comparable to two-thirds of a full moon,There were no further investigations warranted after the sighting,Conclusions suggested the object was probably caused by a reflection or burning material in the atmosphere,The observation lasted for a duration of three to five minutes.
witness description: No witnesses confirmed in the report
